article.headline: Jacksonville 71, Florida Gulf Coast 53
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. -- Ben Smith scored 13 points to lead Jacksonville to a 71-53 victory over Florida Gulf Coast on Saturday. Ayron Hardy, Lehmon Colbert and Marcus Allen each scored 10 for the Dolphins (15-11, 13-4 Atlantic Sun Conference). The win now ties Jacksonville with Belmont at the top of the conference. The Dolphins used an 8-0 run in the first half to take a 21-12 lead with 9:10 remaining, and went into halftime with a 34-23 lead. They then opened the second half with a 14-3 run to go up 48-26 with 13:42 left in the game. Jacksonville led 23 points, as the Eagles never got closer than 14. Florida Gulf Coast (11-20, 7-13) was paced by Derrick O'Neil and Delvin Franklin, who scored 14 points apiece. Kyle Marks chipped in with 10.
